125
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:06,000
Why did I do that?

126
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:11,000
Framing Madam to make your son replace Mr. Tian.

127
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,000
Alright.

128
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:18,000
If you think you're innocent…

129
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,000
Mr. Song.

130
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,000
I think we should report the police.

131
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,000
Let them investigate to find out the truth.

132
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:31,000
And if anyone is found guilty, put the person in jail.

133
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:39,800
Father.

134
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,000
We found Dong.

135
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,000
Dong.

136
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:21,000
Dong is really dead.

137
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:22,300
Madam.

138
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:25,000
You are so cruel and ruthless.

139
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,000
Do you have to kill him?

140
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:35,000
Does this mean Dong didn't drown?

141
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:37,000
Calm down.

142
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:40,000
No one killed Dong. He drowned in the river.

143
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,000
He may be drowned in the water.

144
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:44,000
What are you saying, Mom?

145
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:47,000
Dong sailed away and the boat capsized.

146
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,000
Bua was the one who found the body.

147
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:53,000
Bua, tell me what it is.

148
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:57,000
This morning when I took the boat back from the market.

149
00:15:57,500 --> 00:16:02,000
I saw that there was a body floating in the lotuses over there.

150
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,000
Bua.

151
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,000
Why didn't you tell him

152
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:30,000
that last night we went looking for Dong.

153
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,000
We heard his voice in the back garden.

154
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,000
Last night when I came out to collect my clothes,

155
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:45,000
I did meet Chan and Nuan.

156
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,000
Dong.

157
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:48,000
Dong.

158
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,000
Bua.

159
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:53,000
Did you see Dong pass by?

160
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,000
I don't see him.

161
00:16:56,000 --> 00:17:00,000
But I'm not sure I heard Dong's voice.

162
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,000
What is this pouch?

163
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,000
That's the workers' wages that I prepared.

164
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:37,000
Did Dong steal everyone's wages and fled?

165
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,000
He was so evil.

166
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:44,000
That's why he bought Mud stuff and asked her to go out.

167
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,000
So he actually stole other's stuff.

168
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,000
In fact,

169
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:52,000
After Dong had a fight with Tian.

170
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:54,000
I called him to talk again.

171
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:57,000
But he became aggressive and disrespected me as well.

172
00:17:57,700 --> 00:18:01,000
So I gave him final offer to get out of here.

173
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:04,000
But I didn't think that

174
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:08,000
he would steal the workers' wages and ran away and drowned like this.

175
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,000
This must be your plan.

176
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:18,000
Killing him, putting the wages at him and framed him for stealing money.

177
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:19,000
That's too much, Madam Chan.

178
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:22,000
Use your brain.

179
00:18:22,700 --> 00:18:25,000
How could Madam and I fight Dong?

180
00:18:25,300 --> 00:18:26,000
Look at his body size.

181
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:29,000
That's right. Dong was so strong.

182
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:30,000
Shut up.

183
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:32,000
Yang.

184
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:34,000
Check Dong again.

185
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:37,000
Is there something wrong?

186
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,000
Is there anything more?

187
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,000
No.

188
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:22,000
He must have really drowned

189
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:25,000
because there were no traces of fighting.

190
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:27,000
If you kept quiet about Tian,

191
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:30,000
you wouldn't probably meet an end like this.

192
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:12,000
Then it means Dong stole the workers' money

193
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,000
and ran away,

194
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:16,000
but the ship turned upside down and then drowned.

195
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:20,000
It's a mess.

196
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:21,000
Mr. Song.

197
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,000
Mom.

198
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:44,000
If you don't have evidence about the murder,

199
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:46,000
you shouldn't accuse Madam Li.

200
00:21:46,300 --> 00:21:48,000
Hey, why are you siding with her?

201
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,000
Don't you want the position of the clan leader?

202
00:21:51,300 --> 00:21:52,000
No.

203
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:56,000
I prefer to be a follower. I'm fine now, Mom.

204
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:01,000
Mother.

205
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:04,000
Stop looking for a way to make me take the position from Tian.

206
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:08,000
He is my brother and my benefactor.

207
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:10,000
He also saved my life.

208
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:14,000
If I take the position from him, that means I betray him.

209
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:18,000
So what you're doing now doesn't mean you betray me? Ungrateful son.

210
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:20,000
I really asked you.

211
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,000
You want to be inferior to him for the rest of your life?

212
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,000
Don't you see

213
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:27,000
what it's like to be second?

214
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:32,000
No matter what I say or do, no one listens and believes me.

215
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:34,000
But look at Madam Li,

216
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:36,000
everyone always follows her.

217
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:40,000
That's because her words are reasonable.

218
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:43,000
And look at you, you said everything loud like this, who would believe you?

219
00:22:43,300 --> 00:22:45,000
I didn't yell for no reason.

220
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:47,000
Everything is reasonable,

221
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:50,000
but no one listens to me

222
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,000
because no one care about me.

223
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:56,000
You too. If you were the eldest child,

224
00:22:56,700 --> 00:23:01,000
even if you were a rascal, everyone still respected you.

225
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,000
I must know

226
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:15,000
what Tian’s secret that will shake the position of the clan leader is?

227
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,000
Mother.

228
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,000
Tian.

229
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,000
Come in.

230
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:52,000
I made bamboo pith soup for you.

231
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,000
Thank you my son.

232
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:09,000
Mother.

233
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,000
About Dong's death…

234
00:24:13,500 --> 00:24:16,000
Do you also think that I did it?

235
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:22,000
I said that I talked to him to fire him.

236
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:25,000
He must have been mad, so he stole the money and were drowned while running away.

237
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:31,000
He didn't die because he knew about me, did he?

238
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,000
Of course not.

239
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:37,000
How would he know?

240
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:47,000
When I, Jia and you didn't speak.

241
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:48,000
Yes, Mother.

242
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:51,000
I'm sorry for doubting you.

243
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:56,000
That's okay.

244
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:00,000
Remember that

245
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,000
I love you so much.

246
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:23,000
When you found Dong's body this morning,

247
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:27,000
did you see anything strange?

248
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:31,000
Not at all. It was normal.

249
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:34,000
Why?

250
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:38,000
Don't you think that Dong drowned?

251
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:43,000
I am just wondering.

252
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:46,000
I'm just not sure, so I ask you.

253
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:51,000
Not sure? What's that you're not sure?

254
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:55,500
Or …
Does Mr. Tian really have a secret?

255
00:25:55,500 --> 00:25:59,000
So you suspected that Madam Li killed Dong.

256
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:01,000
There's no secret.

257
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:05,000
If you didn't see anything, that's fine.

258
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:23,000
Hey, how is it? Have you found the evidence of Dong's murder?

259
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,000
No, Madam.

260
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:28,000
I guess there's nothing here.

261
00:26:28,600 --> 00:26:30,000
If I were Madam Li or Jia,

262
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:33,000
I would have destroyed all the evidence.

263
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:38,000
I'm really curious

264
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:40,000
